<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued January 14 at 3:15AM CST until January 15 at 12:00PM CST by NWS Saint Louis</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING
TO NOON CST SATURDAY...
* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations between 4 and 6
inches.
* WHERE...Portions of south central and southwest Illinois, and
portions of east central Missouri.
* WHEN...From 6 PM this evening to Noon CST Saturday.
* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions. The hazardous
conditions could impact the Friday evening commute.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling. In Illinois, the latest
road conditions can be obtained at www.gettingaroundillinois.com. In
Missouri, the latest road conditions can be obtained at
traveler.modot.org/map or by calling 1-888-275-6636.</instruction>
